Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, March 21 (XINHUA) -- Japanese Prime Minister 
Morihiro Hosokawa returned home today after a three-day visit to 
China for talks with Chinese leader on bilateral and 
international issues. 
  During his stay in China, Hosokawa held separate talks with 
Chinese President Jiang Zemin and Premier Li Peng on fostering 
future-oriented and friendly relations between the two countries. 
  The visit, which came at a time when Sino-Japanese ties have 
entered a new stage, will undoubtedly boost the existing 
political and economic cooperation between China and Japan. 

