<H3> <TI>   Protestor Reportedly Arrested in Tiananmen Square </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2103062994 Hong Kong RTHK Radio Four in English 0500 GMT 
21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2103062994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong RTHK Radio Four </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "News at One"] </F>
  [Text] Police in Beijing have arrested at least one person 
who tried to distribute leaflets in Tiananmen Square, and one 
news photographer had his film seized. Witnesses said that they 
saw leaflets being thrown into a crowd in the square, the site 
of the 1989 Beijing massacre. One incident occurred on the 
north side of the square and another took place at the Monument 
to the People's Heroes in the center of the square. There was 
no indication what the leaflets said. One witness saw police 
throw a person into a car and drive off immediately after the 
incident. 

</TEXT>

