<F P=100> Southeast Asia &amp; Pacific </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cambodia's Sihanouk Reportedly Released From Hospital </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2203054394 Hong Kong AFP in English 0507 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> BK2203054394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 22 (AFP) -- King Norodom Sihanouk 
has been released from the Beijing hospital where he was being 
treated for cancer and is "resting" at his residence here, a 
Cambodian source said. 
  The 71-year-old Cambodian monarch, who underwent surgery on 
October 7 to remove a tumor in the prostate area, left the 
hospital "recently" after he "endured the treatment very well." 
  King Sihanouk is to travel to Pyongyang at the end of the 
month to visit his longtime friend, President Kim Il-song, 
before returning to Phnom Penh on April 8 for Khmer New Year. 
  A Western diplomat said that after his anti-cancer 
treatment, 
King Sihanouk had lost his hair but had gained weight. 

</TEXT>

