<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiangsu's Rural Savings Deposits Up </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803072594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0640 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1803072594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanjing, March 18 (XINHUA) -- Savings deposits of 
rural residents in east China's Jiangsu Province amounted to 
51.32 billion yuan as of March 10. 
  Included were 6.2 billion yuan deposited in the bank in the 
first 70 days of this year, a local bank official said. 
  He attributed the rise in savings deposits to the rapid 
development of local rural economy. 
  The booming rural industrial enterprises and service trades 
have become the mainstays of the provincial economy. 
  According to statistics from the Jiangsu Provincial 
Statistics Bureau, rural residents' net income last year 
averaged 1,267 yuan per capita, an increase of 19.4 percent over 
the previous year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

