<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN FAO Farming School Program Initiated in Jiangxi </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1803004994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0041 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1803004994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Nanchang, March 18 (XINHUA) -- The first field 
school for farmers was recently opened in Xinjian County in East 
China's inland Jiangxi Province, starting an inter-state project 
of the Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations 
(FAO) in the province. 
  Xinjian, which was chosen as a site for the comprehensive 
project about the control of insect and other pests, is a key 
rice producing county. 
  With reference to the experience of field schools for 
farmers 
in Indonesia, recommended by FAO, local authorities will open 
similar schools in line with local conditions in an attempt to 
help farmers to deal with pests and treat diseases that endanger 
rice. 
  No classrooms and teaching facilities are needed for such 
schools: farmers mainly study through actual practice under the 
guidance of experts. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

